rule: The knife slides across the surface of the blocks and table.
The pot's shadow is visible (if light source is present).
Leaves move away from the leaf blower.
The sword penetrates the brick wall, causing visible displacement of bricks and debris.
The beer forms a foamy head in the cup.
The tennis ball changes shape and breaks into smaller pieces upon impact with the racket.
The chisel makes contact with the wooden disc.
The clay deforms under the potter's hands.
The spray from the pressure washer impacts the brick wall.
The athletes skating beside the bobsled move their feet, demonstrating visible changes of position.
